<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-217] Tidy up generated data after unit tests are run</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-217</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I tried to compile Mahout on people.apache.org yesterday: The build failed at first, because tests could not generate test data. The reason: Some tests tried to generate test data at /tmp/&amp;lt;mahout-dir&amp;gt;/... - but those directories did exist already and belonged to Sean. Why? Probably because Sean had run the build earlier this year - but tests did not remove the data they generated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed solution: Tests come with setup and with shutdown hooks. We should remove any data when a test is finished and shut down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
