                            <comment id="12789389" author="srowen" created="Fri, 11 Dec 2009 17:03:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree with this. The right approach is a combination of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;implementing tearDown() to do clean up&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;using File.createTempFile() to make temp files, since it&apos;s guaranteed not to conflict&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;calling .deleteOnExit() on temp Files to make sure the JVM just nukes them on exit for sure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Do you recall what exactly the culprit was? I can patch the proximate problem. Is if the fpgrowth business?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12790656" author="isabel" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2009 10:45:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not only fpgrowth. I will take a closer look on Thursday, make a list and post it here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
